        <actionDate>2019-05-22</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2021-01-15T17:55:51Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>Contaminant and Lead Electronic Accounting and Reporting Requirements (CLEARR) for Drinking Water Act of 2019</strong></p> <p>This bill generally revises provisions related to drinking water quality standards. Specifically, the bill </p> <ul> <li>provides for additional inspections of a public water system after certain standards violations; </li> <li>requires notification to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention and local health agencies of serious standards violations; </li> <li>reauthorizes through FY2024 a grant program to assist the public water systems of disadvantaged and underserved communities to comply with drinking water requirements; and </li> <li>allows for grants to community organizations that provide education to minority, tribal, and low-income communities regarding drinking water contaminants. </li> </ul>]]></text>
      </summary>
